  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6597 sitting between max negative gamma at 6590 (-10.96B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+15.72B), dealers are currently in neutral hedging mode but poised to buy any dip toward 6590 and sell any push above 6605. The massive positive gamma wall at 6605 (+15.72B) creates a strong ceiling where dealer selling pressure intensifies, while the PIN regime suggests mean reversion behavior around current levels. The recent GEX surge (-60% in 1min, -89% in 5min) indicates rapidly changing positioning, with key amplification zones at 6590/6580 creating downside risk if breached.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pinned between 6590-6605 with dealers providing liquidity at both ends.",
